fields: Hold on, I'll make you some rice gruel with eggs.
I'll leave the melon here for you.
Here's a special ration of charcoal.
Since it's a child, you should do it at a temple.
The body should be lightly dressed. Use beanstalks for a good fire.
It's a beautiful day today, in spite of it all.
It hasn't changed a bit. It's great to be back home!
We can finally listen to the gramophone!
It's late. Go to sleep now, okay?
The Americans will be arriving any day now. It's disgraceful having these bums here!
Never mind, just throw it away!
You can see it in their eyes.
Air raid! Get to the shelters, please!
The shelter behind the firehouse should be safest!
Be a good girl; try to be patient.
I'd better get over to the shelter.
Be careful, and get over there as soon as you can.
Setsuko, be a good girl and mind Seita.
Never mind us! Get to the shelter!
Mom, do you have your medicine? Right here, don't worry.
I hate the shelter! Well, you'll be sorry if you get blown up by a bomb! Now, get on.
The firehouse shelter can easily take a hit from a 250-kilo bomb. Don't worry about her.
She'll probably go to Niponmatsu Station to find us.
Let's just catch our breath first.
I lost one of my Geta.
I'll buy you a much better one.
Look, that was the civic hall. We ate lunch there once.
Is our house gone too? Probably.
What are we going to do?
Dad will make them pay for this!
Well, it's not like I was the only one who lost his house.
We're all in the same boat.
Mr. Miura got a direct hit. I feel so sorry for him.
The fires are impossible to put out!
When you try to smother them, the oil just spreads more.
It's not her. She's not down here!
Please report to the elementary school for first aid!
Let's go get them washed out at the school.
She'll be at the school. School?
Seita-san, have you seen your mother?
Seita has to go somewhere. Why don't we wait for him?
Seita-san, I've been looking for you. Are you alright?
This is your mother's, isn't it?
She needs to be moved to a real hospital.
I hear Kaisei hospital in Nishinomiya wasn't hit.
My mother has heart trouble. Can she get her medicine? Okay, I'll ask.
I'll be around if you need me.
If there's anything I can do, just ask.
I know! Did you get biscuit ration yet?
Keep this ring in your purse. Don't lose it.
Mom's hurt. She'll get better though.
We'll stay here at the school tonight. Then tomorrow, we'll go to our aunt's home in Nishinomiya.
We're staying upstairs. Will you join us?
Maybe tomorrow, it's too late now.
Watch me, I'm good at this!
We haven't unbandaged her. You don't want to see the body.
Especially in this heat... She'll have to go on the truck today.
In Nishinomiya, we have a distant aunt there.
I think she'll take care of us.
I'd better get back to work. Good luck to you.
How's your mother? Is she in Kaisei Hospital?
Navy folks are so privileged. You get to have a truck help move you over here!
I've laid out bedding and mosquito netting in your room.
Did she give it to me?
Just be careful you don't lose it.
When Mom's a little better, I'll take you to see her.
Herrings, dried bonito, dried potatoes, and eggs. and pickled plums.
You can't get these for anything nowadays.
Soldiers always get the best at times like these.
Anyway, did you stop by the hospital?
I'd like to tell your mother what's been happening. And I could take Setsuko along to visit her.
Mom died while she was still at the school.
Why didn't you tell me right away?
I didn't want Setsuko to know.
You must inform your father at once!
Look! She bought me new Geta!
Make sure you're back soon, kids. Thanks, ma'am.
Don't be scared. They're just bullfrogs.
Setsuko, close your eyes and say "ah."
We're back. What took you so long?
Seita-san, shouldn't you be in school?
Kobe Steel where I was working was destroyed. And my school burned down. There's no place to go.
Well, I hope you've written to your father.
I already sent a letter through Kure Naval Base. When?
Just after we came here. About ten days ago?
He hasn't replied to me either.
Setsuko, be sure to return those scissors.
The more factories we lose, the harder the others have to work.
We're getting ready for when they finally invade.
You're right. That's why food's getting so hard to find.
Our soldiers aren't the only ones who are suffering.
You work for our country's defense too, young lady. You eat up and work as hard as you can!
So, you've taken in a couple of homeless children?
Poor things, to lose their mother when they're so young.
It's hot in here. I hate shelters!
Just hang on. I'm here for you.
Wanna go to the beach? Yeah! Yeah! Let's go!
It's because all the salt and soy sauce is rationed.
This might be a bit cold.
Feels good, right? You won't itch now. Uh-huh.
Grrr, I'm a bear! I'm gonna eat you!
When it gets a little warmer, I'll teach you how to swim.
But I'll get hungry if I swim.
Mother! Were you waiting long? It's good to see you again.
I'm fine, don't worry! Everyone is nice here.
Get up. There's an air raid coming.
Your mother won't be needing her kimono anymore. Why don't you trade it for some rice.
I've been trading off my things bit by bit for food.
You can probably get 15 kilograms of rice for them.
You can't be a soldier if you don't grow up healthy.
Your mother would be glad you didn't just let it go to waste.
No! No! They're Mama's! No! No! They're Mama's!
We'll have a proper rice dinner tonight, Setsuko.
This is for you two to keep.
Here you go. With my daughter and our lodger working late so much, I've felt bad not having rice to give them.
It's great, huh? Real white rice!
You're just gobbling it down tonight, aren't you, Setsuko?
What's wrong? I don't want rice porridge.
Don't we have any more pickled plums?
We finished those off ages ago.
Here's your lunch. Thanks, I'd better get going.
We'll have rice balls for lunch. Just hold on until then.
Enough! You'll have rice porridge for lunch too!
You think a lazy slug like you deserves the same as people who work for our nation?!
You don't share your rice, and now you want more of ours?! That's unacceptable!
You keep saying you want rice, but do you go out and earn it? No. Not even once!
I even give you a little bit of rice, and already you're spoiled!
But that was our rice first.
Oh, so now I'm cheating you?
How dare you say that?! After I take you two orphans in!
Fine! We'll just make our own dinners from now on!
Seita-san, you have other relatives in Tokyo, don't you?
On your mother's side of the family, right?
Problem is, I don't know their address.
Sorry you had to wait so long.
I'm hungry, and I'm thirsty too.
Mom has 7,000 yen saved in the bank.
7,000! That's plenty to live on. We're going to be all right.
I'm telling Dad to write back soon, because you're waiting.
You can't find such a good stove nowadays at any price.
Items are scarce, especially hardware. Can't get those anywhere!
I'll take that comb, and... Do you have an umbrella?
Be careful with that fire. We will!
Mother, did you scold them again?
Yes, but they still refuse to apologize. And that boy even bought a stove. Just to spite me!
Doesn't matter any more. You can relax too.
The next ration should be in July.
I can taste so many flavors!
Grape, strawberry, melon, mint... Drink it all up, Setsuko.
Great, they left me their dishes for me to do.
Seita-san, others here are working for our country. We can't have her loud crying keeping them awake.
With the nightly raids and crying, how can we sleep?!
I want to go home. I hate living with her!
We don't have a home. It was burned.
Don't you realize there's a war going on?!
You two are nothing but trouble for me!
You two pests bring us nothing but trouble!
You're useless in raids. You could just go and live in that cave for all I care!
Nobody comes here. It's sturdy. We can do whatever we want.
It's all right to do that?
Thank you for everything. We're going to go now.
Going...? Where to? We're not sure yet.
Well, take care then. Goodbye, Setsuko!
This will be the front door!
Where is the bathroom going to be?
That can be anywhere. Wanna go somewhere with me?
Do you think you can sell us some food and straw?
I guess, not much left though.
My mouth's watering! Man, am I hungry.
I've heard you can eat frogs.
I'll do the rest. You go wait under the mosquito net.
What's wrong? I left my toothbrush.
One night without it won't matter.
It's getting buggy. You should stay inside the net.
It's dark in there. I'm scared.
I need to go for a pee. Want to come too?
Okay, let's get as many as we can!
Before you were born, I went to a naval review. A naval review?
Uh-huh. Dad was on a cruiser, the Maya. The entire combined fleet was there!
I wonder where Dad is fighting now?
Whatcha doing? Making a grave. Mama's in a grave too.
She said Mama died, and she's in a grave now.
Setsuko, do you remember the cemetery near Nunobiki?
That's where Mama is. Under a big camphor tree...
Why do fireflies have to die so soon?
Hey, I think somebody's living here. Probably lost their house.
A kid lives here. What's this?
Look! Dried frogs! They eat those?!
Nobody I know would ever eat this stuff!
Yuck! Ground soybeans! And I thought the food I got was bad!
I've traded everything for rice, even my mom's kimono. There's nothing left to trade.
Please, I can pay you money for the rice.
This isn't about kimono or money.
I'm a farmer, but even I don't have extra food to share.
Then be wise. Go back to your aunt's.
Everything's rationed nowadays. You can't survive outside of the system.
Just swallow your pride and apologize to her.
Thank you, but we'll try elsewhere.
You're a navy man's son, right? Be strong!
You must eat your beans and millet.
You have to eat! You need to, so you can grow up!
Something is wrong with my tummy.
I'm sorry! Please let me go!
My sister's sick, I just wanted to get her some sugar!
Shut up! Stealing crops is a serious crime in wartime!
I'm sorry! I'll never do it again, I swear!
No, we're going to the police!
Now walk! I hope they lock you up!
My sister is really sick! She has no one but me!
Understood. I'll talk to him and file a report.
Thank you, I'll handle this. You may go.
You've beaten this poor kid around enough.
I'm even tempted to call it...
I-I will be going. Thank you!
Tonight's air raid was in Fukui.
Would you like a drink of water?
Where does it hurt? You must see a doctor and get a shot.
Seita, I have to go to the bathroom.
Brother's gone to the mountain to gather firewood. The grandmother...
This pumpkin's great. Tastes just like sweet bean jelly.
Come on, Dad'll get mad at me if you don't eat.
Once you get better, I'll take you to the beach again.
Now I'll really get you something good to eat, Setsuko!
These were your mother's? Don't make me laugh!
Don't try to pawn off this garbage on me!
And she's been having diarrhea for a while now.
The rash isn't from the heat. Seawater just hurts her skin.
Weakening from malnutrition. Thus, the diarrhea. Okay, next!
Can you give her medicine or a shot?
Medicine? All this child needs is food.
Boy, am I hungry. What do you want to eat?
I'll withdraw all of our savings and buy you all the food you need.
I don't need anything. Please stay home with me.
Don't go! Stay with me! Don't leave me alone!
I'll buy you some good, nourishing food.
Then, I'll never ever leave. I'll always be with you.
There's a typhoon coming? What a joke! Our "divine wind" comes after we've surrendered.
Is it true? The Great Empire of Japan lost?
What about the fleet? They're long gone.
All sunk! Not even a single ship left.
Was my Dad's ship sunk too?!
Is that why he hasn't written?! How should I know?
Damn him! I hate you Dad!
Setsuko, sorry I'm so late. I'll make you some rice.
I bought us some chicken and eggs too!
This is a marble. It's not a fruit drop!
You're getting something better today. Your favorite.
Look, it's a watermelon. I didn't steal it either.
Here, I'll even help you. Now cheer up and eat!
